16/07/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Saturday (15 July) urged the Group of Eight (G-8) nations to intervene to an effort to halt fighting in the Middle East. He condemned the recent kidnapping of Israeli soldiers and Israel's response. Erdogan argued that this new exacerbation of the Middle East conflict would only fuel more terrorist attacks worldwide. (AFP - 16/07/06; AP - 14/07/06) 
